here we traverse the array and store the current max value, whenever we reach a index which is equal to current max value, we can cut the array
till there, because when we sort that part ,that particular element will be adjusted there,so we can split the array till then and continue for next chunk
https://leetcode.com/problems/max-chunks-to-make-sorted/description/

//Approach
class Solution {
public:
    int maxChunksToSorted(vector<int>& arr) {
        int max_val=-1,chunks=0,n=arr.size();
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            if(max_val==-1)
            max_val=arr[i];
            max_val=max(max_val,arr[i]);
            if(i==max_val)
            {
                chunks++;
                max_val=-1;
            }
        }
        return chunks;
    }
};
